description: Biju Janata Dal (BJD) urged for more discussions with political parties regarding the "one nation, one election" initiative following the Union Cabinet's approval of related bills.  BJD's Sasmit Patra highlighted the need for addressing constitutional concerns like hung parliaments or loss of confidence in governments before implementing such a significant change.
title: What happens if there's a hung House, asks BJD

description: Tamil Nadu CM M K Stalin and Kerala CM Pinarayi Vijayan inaugurated the renovated Thanthai Periyar memorial and library at Vaikom. Stalin emphasized creating societal equality, while Vijayan highlighted cooperation amidst encroachment on states' rights.  Both leaders commemorated the Vaikom Satyagraha centenary, a pivotal struggle for equality.
title: Vijayan pushes for 'cooperative federalism' at Periyar memorial

description: Government data reveals significant gender disparity in leadership roles within public sector banks, with men holding most chairman and managing director positions.  While women's representation in legislatures has increased over time, including a rise in Lok Sabha and Rajya Sabha, leadership in financial institutions remains predominantly male.
title: Men hold 10 of 11 lead roles in public sector banks: Govt data

description: Maharashtra Deputy Chief Minister Ajit Pawar and his faction visited NCP chief Sharad Pawar on his birthday, sparking reunion rumors. Both factions, previously engaged in fierce campaigns against each other, discussed the Parbhani violence, Parliament disruption, and cabinet expansion.
title: Ajit meets Pawar Sr on birthday, sparks speculation

description: The Jharkhand High Court has temporarily halted a state law mandating 75% job reservation for locals in private companies.  The court's decision follows a legal challenge by an industry association arguing the law violates constitutional equality principles.  The ruling JMM party plans to appeal the stay, while emphasizing the government's intent to boost local employment.
title: HC stays Jharkhand law on 75% quota for locals in private jobs

description: India voted with 158 other countries at the UN General Assembly for resolutions demanding an immediate ceasefire in Gaza, the release of hostages, and access to humanitarian aid.  The assembly also supported the UN agency for Palestine refugees (UNRWA), despite Israel's ban on its operations, urging Israel to respect international law and allow aid delivery.
title: India votes for UN resolution on immediate Gaza ceasefire

description: Congress criticized the government's clearance of simultaneous polls bills, calling it a diversionary tactic.  They expressed concerns about the bills' impact on federalism and electoral integrity, citing Modi's past actions as inconsistent with the "one nation, one election" slogan.  The party reiterated its stance that the concept violates the Constitution's basic structure.
title: Congress: Bid to shift focus from questions on polls' integrity

description: India's retail inflation eased to 5.5% in November from a 14-month high, driven by moderating food prices.  Industrial output saw a modest 3.5% rise in October. While food inflation slowed, vegetable and edible oil prices remain high.  Experts anticipate a potential rate cut in February if the trend continues, though urban demand needs monitoring.
title: Retail inflation eases to 5.5% in Nov as food prices soften

description: The Union Cabinet approved bills for "one nation, one election," aiming to synchronize Lok Sabha, state, and local body polls.  This move seeks to streamline governance and reduce election-related expenses.  While BJP and allies support the initiative, several parties oppose it, sparking debate about its feasibility and impact on India's democracy.
title: Cabinet greenlights 2 bills for one nation, one poll

description: The Trinamool Congress (TMC) urged Prime Minister Narendra Modi to address Parliament regarding the safety of minorities in Bangladesh.  TMC leader Derek O'Brien's request for a statement from the PM was denied, leading to protests by TMC MPs.  The party emphasized the sensitivity of the situation and demanded clarification on the government's intended actions.
title: TMC wants PM statement on Bangladesh situation, Dhankhar turns down demand

description: Union Culture Minister Gajendra Singh Shekhawat affirmed the government's commitment to safeguarding India's heritage. He highlighted concerns about forces attempting to obstruct the nation's progress, particularly regarding debates surrounding surveys of historical sites.  Shekhawat emphasized the need to investigate these motivations.  He also detailed security measures at ASI-protected monuments, citing deployed personnel and addressing recent vandalism incidents across various states.
title: Govt firm on protecting heritage but can't stop filing of PILs: Minister

description: A mosque on the Uday Pratap College campus in Varanasi is under double lock after a land dispute resurfaced.  Students locked the mosque gates following protests sparked by a waqf board's claim, later withdrawn, on the mosque's land.  The college administration holds the second set of keys, halting prayers and preventing further disputes.
title: Kashi college mosque under double lock after namaz row

description: The Supreme Court will hear a petition challenging a Karnataka High Court decision. The HC quashed criminal proceedings against individuals who shouted "Jai Shri Ram" inside a mosque. The petitioner argues that the HC's decision was premature as the police investigation was incomplete and the act could incite communal disharmony.
title: Do 'Jai Shri Ram' chants in masjid hurt religious sentiment? SC to rule

description: The Supreme Court has paused lawsuits seeking reclamation of temples allegedly converted to mosques during Mughal rule, pending its review of the 1991 Places of Worship Act. This freeze on trial court proceedings, including surveys, sparked opposition from Hindu parties, while the court emphasized its authority to determine the Act's scope.
title: SC: Matter pending before us, will it be just for other courts to take it up?

description: The Indian government is considering a new law to regulate artificial intelligence, addressing ethical concerns and the spread of fake narratives.  IT Minister Ashwini Vaishnaw emphasized the need for societal consensus and balancing freedom of speech with accountability.  The government is also developing indigenous AI tools and technologies to ensure responsible innovation.
title: Govt open to new law to regulate AI, minister tells LS

description: Finance Commission chairman Arvind Panagariya expressed confidence in India's economic rebound, projecting a return to 7% growth and the potential to reach a $6.5-$9 trillion economy within a decade. He attributed this to strong fundamentals and suggested further reforms could boost growth beyond 10%.
title: India to return to 7% growth soon, says Panagariya

description: Union Education Minister Dharmendra Pradhan criticized Rahul Gandhi and the Congress party for their "feudal mindset" and disconnect from the changing Indian landscape. He attributed the BJP's recent electoral successes to public trust in their leadership and policies. Pradhan defended the National Education Policy against accusations of ideological bias and dismissed claims of confrontational federalism.
title: Credibility cornerstone of NDA's polls wins: Dharmendra Pradhan

description: India's first domestically produced chip is expected by mid-2024, as the nation establishes itself as a reliable alternative manufacturing hub.  Five semiconductor production units are currently underway, fueled by new incentives.  These investments, along with social, digital, and public infrastructure development, aim to propel India into the top three global economies by 2028.
title: Made-in-India chip by mid-'25, says Ashwini Vaishnaw

description: A Telangana child welfare committee has cancelled a planned bonding exercise between 15 "rescued" children and the adoptive parents they were separated from due to a trafficking investigation.  The children, aged seven months to four years, will remain in government shelters until legally adoptable.  Authorities decided against the exercise to avoid setting a precedent that could validate illegal adoptions.
title: Telangana CWC drops 'bonding exercise' between kids & couples who bought them

description: The Supreme Court questioned the Chhattisgarh government over the prolonged investigation into the liquor scam case, leading to a heated exchange with the state's counsel. While hearing the bail plea of a former excise official, the court expressed concern over the delay in trial, despite multiple chargesheets filed.
title: SC bar & bench have a heated exchange over bail application

description: Commerce Minister Piyush Goyal expressed confidence in India's economic recovery by the fiscal year-end, citing positive trends in festive spending, rural growth, and infrastructure investment. He projected exports to reach $1 trillion within the next two years and emphasized the government's commitment to structural reforms like the Waqf Amendment Bill and 'one nation, one election' initiative.
title: Growth will be back on track by March: Piyush Goyal

description: TMC MP Sagarika Ghosh submitted a privilege motion against Union minister Kiren Rijiju for derogatory remarks towards opposition leaders. Rijiju's comments deemed opposition MPs "unworthy" of their positions after they moved a no-confidence motion against vice president Jagdeep Dhankhar. Ghosh's motion, backed by 60 opposition MPs, criticizes Rijiju's language and alleged misuse of his office.
title: TMC MP moves privilege motion against Rijiju for ‘insulting oppn’

description: The Supreme Court ruled that mere harassment allegations are insufficient for abetment to suicide charges.  Conviction requires proof that the accused instigated the deceased's fatal step.  The court emphasized the need to establish mens rea, a clear intent to provoke suicide, through specific actions or behaviors beyond mere harassment.
title: Mere allegation of harassment not enough to slap abetment to suicide charge: SC

description: Parliamentary proceedings were disrupted amidst a heated debate between the ruling party and the opposition.  The BJP accused Congress of connections with George Soros and alleged Soros-funded organizations' involvement in anti-India activities.  Opposition members protested against these allegations and raised concerns about the Adani issue, leading to adjournments in both Houses.
title: Houses adjourned again amid ruckus over Soros, Adani issues

description: Trinamool Congress MP Kalyan Banerjee has issued a written apology to Lok Sabha Speaker Om Birla for his comments targeting Union Minister Jyotiraditya Scindia. Banerjee also apologized verbally in the House on Thursday.
title: Kalyan Banerjee submits written apology for remarks against Scindia

description: Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge has moved a no-confidence motion against Rajya Sabha chairman Jagdeep Dhankhar, accusing him of suppressing the opposition's voice and echoing BJP's views. Kharge criticized Dhankhar for praising the RSS and equating the Prime Minister with Mahatma Gandhi, while stifling opposition's right to speak and suspending members.
title: Dhankhar suppressing oppn voice: Congress steps up attack

description: Bengaluru police are searching for the Singhania family in Jaunpur, UP, in connection with the suicide of AI executive Subhash Atul. Atul accused his estranged wife and her family of harassment and extortion amidst an ongoing divorce and child custody battle. The family is currently absconding, leaving their house locked.
title: Karnataka cops fail to find in-laws of techie who killed himself

description: Singer Selena Gomez recently announced her engagement to music producer Benny Blanco, leaving fans buzzing with excitement. The spotlight, however, quickly turned to her dazzling engagement ring, a 4-carat marquise-cut diamond that has captivated audiences on the internet. A diamond expert shared fascinating insights about the ring’s design and significance.
title: Selena Gomez engaged to Benny Blanco: Shows off pricey marquise diamond ring
No damage to Taj Mahal, says govt

description: Two suspected cattle smugglers died in a road accident in Jammu and Kashmir's Samba district after their speeding vehicle crashed while attempting to evade a police checkpoint. A policeman was seriously injured after being struck by the smugglers' vehicle. One of the animals being transported was also killed in the crash.
title: 2 cattle smugglers killed in road accident, not encounter: Samba police

description: Security forces in Bastar killed seven Maoists, including a central committee member, just two days before the Union home minister's visit.  Over 1,000 troops launched a pre-dawn operation in Abujhmarh based on intelligence, leading to an ongoing encounter.  The operation has resulted in the seizure of weapons and ammunition, with the death toll of Maoists reaching 220 this year.
title: Two days ahead of Amit Shah's visit to Chhattisgarh, 7 Maoists shot

description: Home Minister Amit Shah embarks on a three-day Chhattisgarh visit to review Left-Wing Extremism (LWE) strategies.  He will honor the Chhattisgarh police, meet Naxal violence victims and surrendered Maoists, and encourage Bastar Olympics participants.  Shah will also pay tribute to fallen security personnel, inspect development work, and chair a security review meeting focused on eliminating LWE by March 2026.
title: On 3-day trip, Shah to chair security meet, go to former Red stronghold

description: A Kuwait-based NRI allegedly stabbed his 12-year-old daughter's molester to death in Andhra Pradesh, India. He confessed to the murder in a selfie video, claiming police inaction after his wife reported the molestation.  Police deny receiving a complaint and allege a family conspiracy, questioning the father's surrender claims.
title: Man flies down from Kuwait to kill daughter's molester

description: A new report reveals a growing gap between Gen Z's skills and employers' expectations.  While Gen Z feels prepared for the corporate world, HR professionals disagree, citing inadequate college curricula and a lack of practical skills.  The rise of AI further complicates the job market, demanding new skills while traditional hiring practices struggle to adapt.
title: Are degrees officially outdated? AI, skills, and Gen Z take over

description: A fire engulfed City Hospital, an orthopedic care facility in Dindigul, Thursday night, claiming the lives of at least seven people, including a child, primarily due to suffocation.  Around 29 patients were transferred to nearby government hospitals.  Authorities swiftly responded, rescuing six individuals trapped in a lift.  An investigation into the fire's cause is underway.
title: Tamil Nadu: Seven killed as fire breaks out at private hospital in Dindigul

description: 18-year-old Indian chess prodigy D Gukesh has made history, becoming the youngest-ever world chess champion by defeating Ding Liren. Former champion Vladimir Kramnik criticized the match quality, citing a "childish" blunder by Ding and expressing disappointment with the overall play. Kramnik declared it the "end of chess as we know it.
title: 'End of chess...': Ex-world champion on Gukesh vs Liren result

description: Tragedy struck a Dindigul orthopaedic hospital as a fire claimed seven lives, including a child and two women, and injured 20 others. The blaze, likely sparked by a short circuit in the reception area, rapidly engulfed the hospital, leading to suffocation from thick smoke.
title: At least 7 dead, 20 injured in Tamil Nadu hospital fire; rescue ops on

description: The Congress party has revealed its first list of 21 candidates for the 2025 Delhi Assembly elections.  Sandeep Dikshit, son of former CM Sheila Dikshit, will challenge CM Arvind Kejriwal in the New Delhi constituency.  The list features a mix of veteran leaders and fresh faces, aiming to bolster the Congress's presence in the Delhi Assembly.
title: Delhi polls: Cong fields Sandeep Dikshit from Kejriwal's home turf

description: Zomato faces a substantial ₹803.4 crore GST demand from Thane authorities for unpaid taxes on delivery charges between October 2019 and March 2022.  The demand includes a penalty equal to the tax amount. Zomato maintains it's not liable, arguing delivery partners, not the company, provide the service, and plans to appeal the decision.
title: GST department asks Zomato to pay Rs 800 crore in taxes, fines
How Netanyahu is keeping his vow to 'change face of Middle East'

description: Supreme Court overturned a Gujarat high court ruling, acquitting in-laws accused of abetting a woman's suicide. The court emphasized that harassment alone isn't enough for conviction; clear intent to provoke suicide is necessary. While acknowledging alleged cruelty, the court upheld charges, ensuring the trial continues.
title: Mere harassment insufficient for abetment of suicide conviction: SC

description: 18-year-old Indian chess prodigy D Gukesh has made history, becoming the youngest-ever world chess champion. In a thrilling final match in Singapore, Gukesh defeated reigning champion Ding Liren, securing the title with a score of 7.5 to 6.5. He surpasses the previous record held by Garry Kasparov, who won the championship at age 22.
title: Gukesh beats Ding to become youngest world chess champion

description: The assassination of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson sparked a divided national debate. Some view Luigi Mangione, the alleged shooter, as a villain, while others hail him as a folk hero protesting corporate greed in the US healthcare system. Mangione's symbolic gestures, including inscribed bullet casings and a manifesto, amplified public frustration with rising healthcare costs and claim denials.
title: 'Social banditry': Why many Americans are celebrating killing of a CEO

description: D Gukesh won the World Chess Championship. He defeated Ding Liren in a thrilling final match. The 18-year-old made history. He became the youngest world chess champion. Gukesh secured victory after a crucial error by Ding.  Gukesh is the second Indian to win the title. He joins the legendary Viswanathan Anand.
title: Ding Liren's blunder that made Gukesh world chess champion

description: Dr. Mithun Kudalkar, a 39-year-old dental surgeon and accomplished athlete, died hours after completing a 20-mile marathon in Goa. Despite being declared fit by doctors after experiencing discomfort, he collapsed at home.  While the cause remains undetermined, sudden cardiac arrest is suspected.  His running partner noted he appeared fine during the race, only later complaining of acidity.
title: 39 year old dental surgeon dies hours after participating in Goa marathon

description: A quirky Indian wedding invitation has gone viral for its humorous honesty. It playfully requests guests to "complain about the food" and acknowledges the wedding day chaos, including potential traffic jams and a coincidental mass wedding date clash.
title: 'Sharma Ji ke Ladki weds ... ': The wedding card going viral

description: Meta, Facebook's parent company, donated $1 million to Donald Trump's second-term inauguration fund after CEO Mark Zuckerberg met with the president-elect.  Zuckerberg reportedly expressed support for Trump's economic plans, despite past tensions.  This marks a shift from Meta's previous stance of not donating to presidential inaugurations.
title: Olive branch? Zuckerberg's Meta donates $1m to Trump's inauguration fund

description: Mark Zuckerberg's gold-plated Cuban link chain is up for auction, with bids exceeding $40,000.  The proceeds will benefit Inflection Grants, supporting unconventional creative projects.  The winning bidder receives the chain and a personalized authentication video from Zuckerberg. The chain holds sentimental value as Zuckerberg plans to engrave it with a Jewish prayer he sings to his daughters.
title: FB founder Mark Zuckerberg's gold chain is being sold for over $40,000

description: 18-year-old Indian Grandmaster D Gukesh achieved his lifelong dream, becoming the youngest world chess champion by defeating Ding Liren.  He secured victory with 7.5 points against 6.5 in a closely fought final game in Singapore.  Gukesh fulfilled his childhood ambition, claiming the prestigious title and a $1.3 million prize, surpassing Garry Kasparov's previous record.
title: 11-year-old D Gukesh reveals ambition in viral video. Watch

description: Parliament will host a crucial debate on the Constitution.  Prime Minister Modi and home minister Shah will participate.  The opposition plans to raise concerns like the Manipur crisis and caste census.  The ruling party will likely discuss historical events and alleged foreign interference.  This debate offers a platform for both sides to address key national issues.
title: BJP, oppn prepare for fierce Constitution debate on Dec 13
Cash-in-account scheme: Will new poll formula work in Delhi after Maha & J'khand?

description: Kangana Ranaut is set to reprise her role as Rani in the upcoming Queen 2.  Sonakshi Sinha humorously addressed pregnancy rumors after her recent marriage to Zaheer Iqbal.  Kusha Kapila opened up about the impact of her divorce.  Shahid Afridi dismissed past dating rumors with Sonali Bendre.  Shah Rukh Khan lent his voice to Diljit Dosanjh's new song teaser.
title: Kangana to return in Queen 2; Sonakshi shuts down pregnancy rumours: Top 5 news

description: NFL legend Tom Brady recently auctioned off 41 prized possessions, including memorabilia and luxury watches.  The auction featured items like his final Patriots game helmet and a Rolex Daytona 'John Player Special.'  Several Richard Mille and Audemars Piguet watches, worth hundreds of thousands of dollars, highlighted the collection, offering a glimpse into Brady's personal style.
title: Inside Tom Brady’s luxury auction: $900k Rolex & rare NFL memorabilia
Four schoolgirls mowed down by truck in Kerala, CM Vijayan condoles 'tragic' deaths
Iranian singer performs online concert without hijab, faces prosecution

description: 18-year-old Indian Grandmaster D Gukesh etched his name in history, becoming the youngest world chess champion by defeating Ding Liren.  Overwhelmed with emotion, Gukesh celebrated his victory with a unique gesture, resetting the pieces on the board.  His 7.5 points to Ding's 6.5 secured the title in the 14th game, surpassing Garry Kasparov's record. Gukesh graciously acknowledged Ding's valiant fight.
title: D Gukesh puts his pieces back in a unique victory celebration. Watch

description: Farmer leader Jagjit Singh Dallewal marked his 17th day of a hunger strike at the Khanauri border, protesting for farmer demands including an MSP guarantee law. In an open letter to PM Modi, Dallewal highlighted the government's unfulfilled promises regarding MSP and the Swaminathan Commission's recommendations, citing instances from 2011, 2014, and 2018.
title: Bloody thumbprint: Farmer leader's unique message to PM Modi

description: 18-year-old Indian chess prodigy D Gukesh made history on Thursday, becoming the youngest-ever World Chess champion. He defeated China's Ding Liren in a thrilling final match in Singapore, leading to emotional reaction from him and celebrations in India. Gukesh won three games to Liren's two across 14 played.
title: How much prize money did Gukesh win?

description: The Union Cabinet approved the One Nation One Election bill, likely to be tabled in Parliament next week. The opposition INDIA bloc criticised the move as an attack on federalism and democracy, while some parties expressed scepticism about its feasibility. The NDA government and its allies welcomed the bill as a resource-saving measure.
title: Big row over ONOE as Centre gets ready to table bill

description: Following President Bashar al-Assad's ouster and the rebel takeover of Damascus, Syria's constitution and parliament will be suspended for three months.  A new "Salvation Government" has appointed Mohammed al-Bashir as interim prime minister.  A committee will review and amend the constitution during this transition, with a focus on upholding the rule of law and existing freedoms.
title: New Syria govt to suspend constitution, parliament for 3 months

description: The Supreme Court halted new lawsuits against the 1991 Places of Worship Act during its ongoing hearing.  It also prohibited lower courts from issuing survey orders in related cases.  The government has four weeks to respond to petitions challenging the Act's provisions, particularly the August 15, 1947, cut-off date for maintaining religious character.
title: 3 key decisions by SC on pleas against Places of Worship Act

description: Advocate Ashwini Upadhyay challenged the Places of Worship Act, 1991, arguing the need for surveys at disputed religious sites.  He asserted a place's religious character can't be determined by mere observation. The Supreme Court restrained all courts from ordering surveys in such cases while it reviews the Act's constitutionality.
title: 'No law can legalise work of Babar': Lawyer on plea against PoW Act

description: A Bengaluru techie, Atul Subhash, tragically died by suicide, alleging harassment by his wife and her family. Following the incident, his mother-in-law and brother-in-law have reportedly fled their Uttar Pradesh residence. Subhash's brother filed an FIR accusing them of abetment to suicide and extortion, citing demands for large sums of money.
title: Techie suicide case: Accused in-laws 'flee' Jaunpur home

description: 50 Cent reignites his feud with Jay-Z, casting shade on the upcoming Super Bowl LIX amidst controversy surrounding Roc Nation's involvement.  While Jay-Z's partnership with the NFL has revolutionized the halftime show, recent accusations against him have sparked speculation about the event's future, with 50 Cent adding fuel to the fire through social media and interviews.
title: Jay-Z's Super Bowl Halftime Show in Jeopardy?: 50 Cent Throws MAJOR Shade

description: Rajya Sabha saw a clash between the ruling and opposition parties.  Congress leader Kharge accused Chairman Dhankar of stifling opposition voices.  BJP connected Congress to investor George Soros.  TMC MP Sagarika Ghose filed a privilege motion against minister Kiren Rijiju for his remarks on opposition members.  The house witnessed heated exchanges between members.
title: Kharge claims Dhankar 'persistently heckles' oppn in Rajya Sabha

description: South Africa's SA20 league is aiming to emulate the success of the Indian Premier League (IPL) by attracting top international talent and providing a platform for young South African players. The league's second season saw strong attendance, and the addition of India's Dinesh Karthik, for the third edition, is expected to further boost viewership.
title: 'Important to have strong teams, there is strength-vs-strength': Kallis

description: Uttar Pradesh Deputy CM Brajesh Pathak accused Rahul Gandhi of attempting to "incite people" and "spread anarchy" during his visit to the Hathras gang-rape victim's family. Pathak called Gandhi "confused" and suggested he attend a meditation center.  Gandhi met the family privately and departed without addressing reporters. Congress shared a letter from the victim's father requesting justice, prompting Gandhi's visit.
title: 'Trying to incite people': UP's deputy CM on Rahul's Hathras visit

description: In 1998, Elon Musk accurately predicted the internet's evolution into the ultimate media platform, encompassing all traditional forms.  His vision, initially deemed "crazy," foresaw the rise of streaming, social media, and interactive platforms, transforming how we consume and share content.  This foresight highlights the power of recognizing technological trends and their societal impact.
title: Elon Musk's 1998 prediction that he says he was called 'crazy' for

description: Sunil Gavaskar advises Virat Kohli to avoid playing deliveries outside the off-stump until settled, emulating Sachin Tendulkar's Sydney approach.  He believes Australia holds the momentum going into the third Test after their Adelaide victory disrupted India's earlier gained momentum.
title: Gavaskar's key tips to Kohli: 'Follow Sachin's approach'

description: The James Webb Space Telescope (JWST) detected frozen water and other volatile compounds within a protoplanetary disk 1,300 light-years away in the Orion Nebula. This discovery provides crucial insights into early planetary formation and the potential for life beyond our solar system. JWST's NIRCam instrument observed these compounds, suggesting that the disk may contain the building blocks for habitable planets.
title: NASA's Webb finds water in protoplanetary disk beyond our solar system

description: India's November 2024 CPI inflation eased to 5.48%, falling within the RBI's target range.  Food inflation also decreased to 9.04%.
title: November CPI inflation eases to 5.48%; IIP growth rate at 3.5% for October
7 Maoists killed during encounter in Chhattisgarh

description: Sanjiv Goenka, owner of Lucknow Super Giants, praised MS Dhoni's exceptional leadership and mentorship in a recent podcast. Goenka highlighted Dhoni's ability to reinvent himself and nurture young talent like Matheesha Pathirana. He also recounted Dhoni's patient interaction with his young grandson and admired Dhoni's handling of past controversies. At CSK, Dhoni's guidance has created a culture of consistency, loyalty, and excellence, making the franchise one of the most respected in the IPL.
title: 'Unke jaisa leader...': MS Dhoni's leadership lauded ahead of IPL 2025

description: ISRO successfully hot-tested its CE20 cryogenic engine with an innovative nozzle protection system.  The test validated a multi-element igniter, crucial for engine restart, and achieved all performance parameters.  This enhanced engine, powering the LVM3, is set to boost India's space exploration capabilities for Gaganyaan and future missions.
title: Isro's CE20 Cryogenic Engine passes critical sea-level hot test

description: The Union Cabinet approved the 'One Nation, One Election' bill, aiming for concurrent elections nationwide. A high-level committee, chaired by former President Kovind, found that simultaneous elections would enhance policy consistency and voter participation. The bill, based on extensive research and stakeholder consultations, is expected in Parliament next week.
title: Cabinet clears ONOE bill, likely to be tabled in Parliament next week

description: Manipur CM N. Biren Singh assured ongoing efforts by central and state governments to find a permanent solution to the state's crisis, acknowledging the fragile situation and the time required. He addressed the re-imposition of AFSPA, stating the government's request for its withdrawal.
title: Can Manipur crisis be solved? What CM Biren Singh said

description: Google's Project Astra, unveiled at I/O 2024, aims to revolutionize user interaction with a universal AI assistant. CEO Sundar Pichai showcased a prototype, highlighting its multimodal capabilities on smartphones and smart glasses. The AI processes text, voice, and visual input, offering a personalized experience akin to Tony Stark's futuristic interface.
title: ‘This puts Google way ahead ... ’: Paytm CEO congratulates Sundar Pichai

description: Lucknow Super Giants owner Sanjiv Goenka expressed well wishes for KL Rahul after the batter's transfer to Delhi Capitals. Goenka called Rahul a "decent and honest person" and part of his family, despite a tense exchange between them after a match last season. Rahul also spoke about the incident, saying he sought a fresh start and more freedom.
title: 'Shareef insaan hai': Goenka opens up about Rahul's exit

description: TMC MP Sagarika Ghose submitted a privilege motion against Parliamentary Affairs Minister Kiren Rijiju, endorsed by 60 opposition MPs.  Ghose accused Rijiju of making derogatory remarks, stating opposition members were "not worthy" of being in the house.  This follows opposition criticism of Vice President Jagdeep Dhankhar and a no-confidence motion filed against him.
title: 'Insulting remarks': Privilege motion moved against Kiren Rijiju

description: Union minister Nitin Gadkari acknowledged a rise in road accidents, contrary to his initial goal of a 50% reduction. He highlighted human behavior and lack of lane discipline as contributing factors, citing improper truck parking as a major concern.
title: 'Try to hide my face': Gadkari's big confession in Lok Sabha

description: Maharashtra's cabinet expansion is scheduled for Saturday, December 14th, as announced by Deputy CM Ajit Pawar. The BJP is expected to secure 20 ministerial positions, while Shiv Sena and NCP will likely receive 10 each. Ministerial terms may be limited to two and a half years, subject to performance reviews.
title: Maharashtra cabinet expansion on December 14, says deputy CM Ajit Pawar

description: Indian batting legend Sunil Gavaskar played a historic Test match innings 43 years ago. He batted for over 11 hours, scoring 172 runs against England. This feat broke his own record for the longest innings by an Indian batsman. The match in Bangalore eventually ended in a draw.
title: 708 minutes for 172 runs: A truly 'marathon' Test knock

description: The Lok Sabha approved a bill allowing bank account and locker holders to designate up to four nominees.  This change simplifies asset distribution after death.  The bill awaits Rajya Sabha approval and presidential assent for implementation.
title: New bank account, locker rules soon? Check what’s about to change

description: Microsoft announced an $800 million impairment charge due to General Motors' termination of its Cruise autonomous vehicle program.  GM's decision, a reversal from earlier optimistic projections, will impact Microsoft's second-quarter earnings.  The automaker will discontinue the robotaxi business, redirecting its autonomous vehicle technology towards personal car operations.  This move also affects other investors like Honda.
title: Microsoft to take $800 million hit from this sudden U-turn by General Motors

description: Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal announced a monthly payment of Rs 1,000 for registered women in Delhi. This amount will increase to Rs 2,100 after the upcoming elections. Kejriwal cited a previous announcement delayed due to his imprisonment, emphasizing the importance of supporting women and their role in families and society.
title: Rs 2,100 to every Delhi woman if voted to power: Kejriwal's big poll promise

description: Rahul Gandhi visited the family of the 2020 Hathras rape victim after receiving a letter from the victim's father. The letter detailed the family's continued struggle for justice, unfulfilled promises of government aid, and the trauma of living under constant security. The father expressed feeling imprisoned and unable to work while the accused are free.
title: 'Don't know whose body was burnt': Hathras rape victim's family to Rahul

description: A recent survey of Delhi-NCR car owners reveals a shocking disregard for Pollution Under Control (PUC) certificates. 63% are unaware of their certificate status, and a further 11% don't even know what a PUC is. This ignorance is alarming given vehicular emissions contribute significantly to the region's hazardous air quality.
title: 63% Delhi-NCR drivers clueless about this document, risk Rs 10k fine

description: Australian all-rounder Mitchell Marsh anticipates facing Jasprit Bumrah in the upcoming Brisbane Test.  Marsh believes an aggressive approach is key against the world's best bowler. He also backed Steve Smith's return to form and emphasised Australia's focus on the present, aiming to build on their Adelaide victory and take a 2-1 series lead.
title: How to tackle Bumrah? Marsh reveals his mantra

description: Following a 10-wicket defeat in Adelaide, Australia levelled the series 1-1 in the Border-Gavaskar Trophy. Sunil Gavaskar believes the momentum has shifted to Australia ahead of the Gabba Test. Harbhajan Singh emphasizes the series' unpredictable nature, highlighting India's need to secure victories in at least two of the remaining matches, ideally starting with Gabba.
title: Sunil Gavaskar explains why the momentum is with Australia, not India

description: Prince William and Princess Kate are stepping up.  King Charles faced health issues. Kate battled and overcame cancer. William increased his royal duties. The royal couple is now focusing on their future as monarchs.  Palace staff are working on succession plans. The royal family is adapting to change. They are prioritizing family time.
title: Are Prince William, Kate Middleton preparing to be king, queen?

description: The Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) criticised the BJP-led government over Delhi's "deteriorating" law and order.  AAP highlighted rising crime, including a recent murder and bomb threats, citing these incidents as evidence of inadequate security.  AAP MP Sanjay Singh demanded a Rajya Sabha discussion on the issue, emphasizing the risks to residents, including parliamentarians and foreign dignitaries.
title: 'Criminals no longer fear...': AAP's 'Mogambo' jibe at Amit Shah

description: Virat Kohli is poised to surpass Rahul Dravid's Test run record against Australia in the upcoming Brisbane Test. Meanwhile, Shubman Gill aims to overtake Yuvraj Singh's career Test run tally and Rishabh Pant is on the verge of eclipsing Sunil Gavaskar and ML Jaisimha's run records at the Gabba. The third Test begins on December 14.
title: When Virat scores his second run in Brisbane, he will...

description: A Kerala man fell victim to a WhatsApp investment scam, losing ₹4.05 crore over two-and-a-half months.  Lured by promises of high returns through share trading via the "Br-Block Pro" app, he made multiple payments.  Upon realizing he couldn't withdraw funds, he filed a complaint with the cyber police, who are now investigating.
title: Kerala man loses Rs 4 cr in two-and-a-half months in WhatsApp scam

description: The Chandigarh Commission for Protection of Child Rights (CCPCR) has advised singer Diljit Dosanjh against performing songs promoting alcohol, drugs, and violence at his December 14 Chandigarh concert.  The commission cited potential negative impacts on children and referenced WHO sound level guidelines.  They also requested no alcohol be served to those under 25, citing legal ramifications.
title: Diljit Dosanjh told not to promote themes of alcohol, drugs at Chandigarh concert

description: A Bengaluru techie, Atul Subhash, died by suicide, leaving a note alleging harassment by his wife, her family, and a judge.  He detailed marital discord and legal battles.  His family demands justice and action against the accused, raising concerns about corruption within the legal system. Police are investigating the allegations.
title: Judge 'laughed' when estranged wife told Bengaluru techie to commit suicide

description: Netflix co-founder Marc Randolph revealed his unconventional definition of success.  Prioritizing family over relentless work, he championed a 30-year tradition: Tuesday date nights with his wife.  His true achievement?  Building companies while maintaining a strong marriage and family life, proving balance is key.
title: Netflix co-founder Marc Randolph shares his definition of true success

description: The Year of the Wood Snake in 2025 promises introspection, wisdom, and growth.  Each Chinese zodiac sign will experience unique challenges and opportunities. Rats and Oxen find stability, while Rabbits and Dragons enjoy prosperity.  Snakes face obstacles, but Horses, Goats, and Roosters thrive. Monkeys, Dogs, and Pigs navigate varied landscapes of luck and relationships.
title: Chinese Horoscope 2025: The Year of Wood Snake, Check all zodiac signs

description: The National Investigation Agency (NIA) conducted searches at 19 locations across five states, targeting suspected hideouts linked to the Pakistan-based terrorist group Jaish-e-Mohammed. The operation follows a previous raid two months ago that resulted in the arrest of a key suspect.
title: 'Suspects motivating youth into committing terror attacks': NIA raids 19 sites

description: Pushpa 2: The Rule continues its box office reign, becoming the highest-grossing Indian film of 2024 with Rs 1,062 crore globally.  The Allu Arjun and Rashmika Mandanna starrer has netted ₹689.44 crore in India, surpassing Kalki 2898 AD.  The film's success has sparked speculation about whether it can overtake Dangal's record. Rashmika Mandanna expressed gratitude for the overwhelming fan support.
title: 'Pushpa 2' box office collection Day 8

description: Jasprit Bumrah dispelled fitness concerns with a full training session at the Gabba ahead of the third Test against Australia.  He bowled at full tilt, including a spell with the new ball to Rohit Sharma, hinting at Sharma's return to the opening slot. Bumrah had an injury scare when he broke down briefly during the second Test in Adelaide
title: Bumrah returns to bowl in the nets, dismissing injury fears

description: Rohit Sharma's experiment at No. 6 in the Adelaide Test failed, prompting his return to the opening spot for the third Test against Australia at The Gabba.  The out-of-form Indian captain practiced facing the new ball in the nets, indicating his likely return to open alongside Yashasvi Jaiswal, with KL Rahul potentially moving to the middle order.
title: 3rd Test: Rohit Sharma may open the batting at Gabba against Australia

description: An Army jawan reportedly died by suicide using his service rifle while on duty in Jammu and Kashmir's Rajouri district.  This follows a separate incident where a policeman fatally shot a colleague before taking his own life in Udhampur district, raising concerns about mental health within the security forces.
title: Army personnel shoots self in Jammu and Kashmir's Rajouri

description: A twin-engine plane crashed onto a Texas highway Wednesday afternoon, injuring four and damaging three vehicles. The Piper PA-31, carrying only the pilot, broke apart upon impact near Victoria, scattering debris.  Three people suffered minor injuries, while one required more extensive care.  A witness described seeing the plane wobble before crashing. The FAA is investigating the incident.
title: Watch: Propeller plane crashes into vehicles at Texas highway

description: The Supreme Court upheld the Department of Homeland Security's broad power to revoke visas, even for alleged fraud, barring judicial review.  This reinforces agency discretion in immigration matters, potentially leaving petitioners vulnerable while deterring fraud.  While critics raise concerns, the ruling allows petitioners to reapply or challenge future decisions if circumstances change.
title: US Supreme Court upholds discretionary revocation of visa applications

description: Luigi Mangione, accused of killing UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson, has received over $40,000 in donations for his legal defense. The fundraising page and merchandise sales reflect divided public opinion, with some viewing Mangione as a folk hero protesting the US healthcare system, while others condemn the act as a dangerous precedent.
title: ‘Justifiable homicide’: Donations pour in for suspected CEO killer’s legal defence

description: The World Chess Championship between D Gukesh and Ding Liren is level at 6.5 points each after 13 games.  With one game remaining, the 18-year-old Indian challenger aims to secure victory in the final classical game to avoid tiebreakers, where the reigning champion, Liren, holds a significant advantage due to his superior rapid and blitz rankings.
title: Explained: Why Gukesh wants to end Liren's reign in Game 14 itself

description: A video allegedly reveals a massive captagon warehouse near Damascus, reportedly linked to Syrian President Bashar al-Assad's brother, Maher al-Assad.  The discovery supports accusations of the regime's involvement in the drug's production and export, a growing concern across the Middle East and Europe.
title: Watch: Video shows drug warehouse in Syria filled with 'poor man's cocaine'
From party animal to murder suspect: New video of Mangione reveals his wild college days

description: Saudi Arabia won the right to host the 2034 FIFA World Cup, sparking excitement and questions. Key concerns include stadium locations, tournament dates and women's access to matches. Alcohol prohibition, worker rights, and Israel's potential participation are also significant issues. At the FIFA Congress, the 2030 edition was also formally approved.
title: Saudi Arabia to host World Cup: What we know, what we don't

description: Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma's potentially last Australian tour is under scrutiny due to their recent inconsistent performances.  Former Australian captain Greg Chappell emphasizes the need for strong selection panels to make tough decisions about aging players, even stalwarts, as lucrative contracts can influence players' decisions to continue playing despite declining form.
title: Focus on Virat, Rohit: 'Need right selectors for tough chat'

description: Rohit Sharma faces immense pressure as captain and batsman in the upcoming Brisbane Test. His leadership and batting form have been under scrutiny following India's recent losses. Former Australian cricketer Simon Katich highlighted Jasprit Bumrah's superior captaincy during the Perth Test, contrasting it with Rohit's less effective tactics in Adelaide.
title: Rohit Sharma's captaincy, batting under the scanner

description: Rahul Gandhi visited the family of the 2020 Hathras rape victim, sparking criticism from UP Deputy CM Brajesh Pathak.  Pathak accused Gandhi of exploiting the situation and inciting unrest.  Four years later, the victim's family still awaits justice, holding onto her ashes.  They express frustration over unfulfilled promises and the acquittal of three accused, highlighting their ongoing struggle.
title: Rahul Gandhi heads to Hathras amid Sambhal row

description: A BEST electric bus driver in Mumbai, with only ten days of training and no prior electric vehicle experience, lost control, injuring 42 and killing seven.  CCTV footage shows him escaping with backpacks after the crash.  Authorities are investigating and reviewing driver training and safety protocols, including mandatory breathalyzer tests.
title: 'Collected backpacks, jumped out': Footage shows BEST driver fleeing after crash

description: Queen Camilla's recent absence from royal engagements sparked health concerns. Her son, Thomas Parker Bowles, revealed on a podcast that she's recovering from a persistent bug caught during an overseas tour. Overexertion worsened her condition, leading to pneumonia and subsequent fatigue. The Queen missed key events like Remembrance Day and parts of a Qatari state visit.
title: Queen Camilla’s son gives update on her health and ongoing illness

description: Opposition leaders, including Kapil Sibal, criticized Vice President Jagdeep Dhankhar's role as Rajya Sabha chairman, calling it a "sad day for democracy."  They accused Dhankhar of bias towards the ruling party and disrupting House proceedings.  A no-confidence motion against Dhankhar, signed by 60 opposition MPs, was submitted, while Dhankhar warned of efforts to "disintegrate" the country.
title: History will never forgive those not allowing level playing field: Sibal

description: First lady Jill Biden clarified a remark about holiday "joy" after it was linked to Kamala Harris's past campaign. Tensions between the Biden and Harris families were apparent at the Kennedy Center Honors, where they seemingly avoided interaction. Meanwhile, Jill Biden had a pleasant exchange with Donald Trump at the Notre Dame reopening in Paris.
title: 'You're all reading into that': Jill Biden clarifies after telling crowd to 'feel joy' amid Harris's loss

description: Luigi Mangione, 26, faces murder charges for the death of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson.  Police linked Mangione to the crime through DNA, fingerprints, a matching 3D-printed pistol, and surveillance footage.  Inscribed shell casings and Mangione's writings suggest a motive tied to corporate criticism, though he denies involvement.
title: UnitedHealthcare CEO killing: What is the evidence against Luigi Mangione?

description: India's pace attack struggled in the Adelaide pink-ball Test, raising concerns about the bowling combination for the match in Brisbane. Nitish Reddy might have to sit out to accommodate a specialist fast bowler, with Akash Deep the likely replacement. The third Test begins on December 14, with the five-Test series evenly poised at 1-1.
title: Over to Gabba, with India needing a bowling re-think

description: A Bengaluru automobile executive, Subhash Atul, died by suicide.  He left a note and video blaming his estranged wife and in-laws.  The wife's family denies involvement.  A legal battle over divorce and child custody was ongoing.  Atul's family accused Nikita's family of demanding money.  Nikita had previously filed a dowry harassment complaint against Atul and his family.
title: Techie suicide: Atul's kin demanded Rs 10L leading to my father's death, says estranged wife
How years of feud with Trump forced FBI director Wray to resign: Timeline

description: India hopes Rishabh Pant can recreate his 2021 Gabba heroics as they face Australia again.  Pant's aggressive style, predating "Bazball," was instrumental in India's historic win.  However, Pant's form has been inconsistent since his return from injury, raising questions about his ability to deliver another miracle.
title: 3rd Test: Chasing miracles with Rishabh Pant at Gabba

description: South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol defended his declaration of martial law, apologized for the deployment of troops, and vowed to fight "until the very last minute."  He faces an impeachment motion and a criminal investigation following the dramatic events, which included the arrests of the former defense minister and police chief.
title: 'Will fight until last minute': South Korean president defends martial law
Trump invites China's Xi Jinping to attend inauguration: Reports
ChatGPT down: Global service disruption reported; OpenAI responds
Buy or sell: Five stocks on brokerages’ radar for today
Luigi Mangione's traditional Indian attire sparks social media buzz: 'Luigi Maganlal'

description: Elon Musk's net worth soared past $400 billion, a first, fueled by Tesla's record high and a SpaceX share sale.  His fortune surged by a record $62.8 billion in a single day.  Trump's pro-business policies and Musk's new government role are credited with boosting investor confidence. SpaceX's valuation reached $350 billion, making it the world's most valuable private startup.
title: Elon Musk's net worth tops $400 billion, a historic first

description: Pushpa 2, starring Allu Arjun and Rashmika Mandanna, nears Rs 700 crore net India collection in just seven days. The film earned Rs 42 crore on its first Wednesday, boasting a global gross exceeding Rs 1000 crore. Its success surpasses Kalki 2898 AD and Stree 2, with analysts predicting further box office records. ETimes rated the film 3.
title: ‘Pushpa 2’ collection: Allu Arjun starrer inches towards Rs 700cr mark in India
Donald Trump named Time's Person of the Year for second time

description: Travis Head's dominant 140 in the second Test against India leveled the Border-Gavaskar Trophy.  Former cricketers analyzing Head's performance advised India to exploit his perceived weakness against short-pitched bowling, especially early in his innings, at the upcoming Gabba Test. They suggested targeting his leg side and tempting him with deliveries outside off-stump to induce catches behind the wicket.
title: 'We are coming at you...': How India should tackle Travis Head at Gabba

description: The opposition is initiating a motion in the Rajya Sabha to remove Allahabad HC judge Shekhar Kumar Yadav over controversial comments on a uniform civil code and Muslims. They accuse Yadav of hate speech and violating judicial ethics by publicly expressing political views.
title: Oppn likely to move for removal of Allahabad HC judge

description: Citizens, including prominent figures, have filed applications supporting the Places of Worship Act in the Supreme Court, emphasizing its role in safeguarding secularism and communal harmony. They argue that the challenge to the law ignores historical precedents of temple demolitions across religions and aims to prevent communal conflict.
title: Supreme Court to take up today validity of Places of Worship Act
